                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 11.  <span>Different activation of eIF2α phosphorylation by VSV and poliovirus infections.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec11.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec11.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>HeLa cells were infected with VSV for 4 h, infected with poliovirus for 4 h, or treated with 1 µM of thapsigargin for 1 hour. Cytoplasmic protein extracts from these and control cells were analyzed with Abs against eIF2α and phosphorylated form of eIF2α (panel A). Same membrane was analyzed with Abs against VSV P- protein and poliovirus capsid proteins (panel B).</p>
